Can this instead be three separate commits? These descriptions would make a nice subject line for the respective patches. "Code clean up." isn't terribly expressive.
Will split into 3 separate commits.
Done
We're no longer logging these?  Might be fine, but you should've mentioned it in your commit message.
Done
Aren't these items redundant?  Do we have any PMBUS devices that don't support PEC?

I am not sure about devices which does not support PEC. 
But from code perspective I have observed that all calls to getRawPmbusCommand uses same value for doEnablePec. 

So we can remove this argument. 
Will address this.

If we don't need support for it yet, there's no need to have a parmaeter.  Once we have a device that needs either of these, we can add them back.  Doing it in this order makes it more clear why that support exists, and eliminates dead code from upstream.
Done

processReading (old code) was called from read function for every read cycle, which means the switch case is performed for all read operation. 

setReadFunction is only called once per sensor during init.
And from read function we use the pre initialized function pointer to access the correct decoding method. 

For readability of the code, I can define functions like "processByte0Reading" (as per your comment) and assign that to function pointer instead of using lambda function.
Done
Why was this moved?  The old location is closer to where it was used, so it seems like the old one was better?
Will bring it back to old location.
Done
Possible nullptr defreference.
Will address this.
Done
This section has some great cleanups.
Done
Overall, looks like a very good cleanup.  Needs a few minor things done, then it should be good to go.
This variable is only used in one place.  Please declare it in the place where it's used.
Done
Per the coding standard, all of these should be enum class, not enum.
Done
typo
Done
Does this have an enumeration it could use?
Done

Booleans in an API make for very difficult to read code.  Also, in general default parameters are discouraged, as they obfuscate intent in the call site.

Per the last comment "doEnablePec" isn't required (all pmbus devices support PEC) so that needs removed for the moment.

Can you please add

enum class AddressMode{
   8Bit,
   11Bit,
}

and use that for the isExtendedDeviceAddress.

In two places getRawPmbusCommand is called with doEnablePec as true. Rest all places it is called with doEnablePec as false. 

As this is a clean up code I do not want to change the behavior of existing code. If doEnablePec needs to be removed that can be taken in a different PR.
Needs range checked.
Done

Please simplify this to

commandByes.insert(commandBytes.end(), pmbusCommand.begin(), pmbusCommand.end());
Done
